the former comptroller for the new york botanical garden in the bronx was charged yesterday with embezzling at least 170000 from the non profit organization a spokesman for bronx district attorney robert t johnson said last night sandra smith 48 of clayton county nc who had earned 70000 a year as comptroller was arraigned on multiple charges of grand larceny and criminal possession of stolen property she could face additional charges said the spokesman steven reed adding that it is believed she took a total of at least 300000 from charitable donations to the garden which receives public and private funding ms smith who resigned after working at the garden from october 1999 and september 2000 allegedly used the money to pay credit car bills and for car repairs a routine audit a year after she resigned discovered that the money was missing mr reed said adding that bail was set at 150000 tina kelley nyt

